    {
      "title": "PROTOCOL: Plaintext Equivalence Test (PET)\nDue to:\nJakobsson and Juels [51]\nPrincipals:\nTabulation tellers TT_i\nc_j = \\mathsf{Enc}(m_j; K_{\\mathsf{TT}}) = (a_j, b_j) \\text{ for } j \\in \\{1, 2\\}\nPublic input:\nPrivate input (TT_i): Private key share x_i\nLet R = (d, e) = (a_1/a_2, b_1/b_2)\nOutput:\nIf m_1 = m_2 then 1 else 0\n1. TT_i: z_i \\leftarrow \\mathbb{Z}_q^*; (d_i, e_i) = (d^{z_i}, e^{z_i})\n2. TT_i: Publish Commit(d_i, e_i)\n3. TT_i: Barrier: wait until all commitments are available\n4. TT_i: Publish (d_i, e_i) and proof EqDlogs(d, e, d_i, e_i)\n5. TT<sub>i</sub>: Verify all commitments and proofs\n6. Let c' = (\\prod_i d_i, \\prod_i e_i)\n7. All TT: Compute m' = \\mathsf{DistDec}(c') using private key shares\n8. If m' = 1 then output 1 else output 0",
      "heading_level": null,
      "page_id": 3,
      "polygon": [
        [
          205.5,
          397.546875
